</script><h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Continuity">Continuity</span><span class="editsection"><a href="/wiki/How_Lily_Stole_Christmas?action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit Continuity section"><img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D" class="sprite edit-pencil" />Edit</a></span></h2>
<ul><li>Future Ted censors the story for his kids for the first time, substituting some "very bad words" for "grinch" and "fudge".
</li><li>Barney says "When I start feeling sick, I stop being sick and be awesome instead. True story." This is an altered version of the solution to sadness he describes inÂ <i><a href="/wiki/Where_Were_We%3F" title="Where Were We?"><span style="cursor: help;" title="Where Were We? (2x01) - Marshall is depressed over his and Lily&#39;s break up. Things get worse when he learns she might be back in town.">Where Were We?</span></a></i>.
</li><li>Ted was previously shown to have taken Marshall's side in his and Lily's break-up inÂ <i>Where Were We?</i>Â andÂ <i><a href="/wiki/The_Scorpion_and_the_Toad" title="The Scorpion and the Toad"><span style="cursor: help;" title="The Scorpion and the Toad (2x02) - Barney helps Marshall get back into the singles&#39; scene. Lily is back in town and Ted and Robin try to learn the truth about how she feels about the breakup.">The Scorpion and the Toad</span></a></i>.
</li><li>Ted's middle name, Evelyn, is first mentioned in this episode.
</li><li>Ted's cousinÂ Stacy and her six children were previously mentioned inÂ <i><a href="/wiki/Brunch" title="Brunch"><span style="cursor: help;" title="Brunch (2x03) - Ted discovers that his parents are keeping a secret from him after his dad acts as Barney&#39;s wingman. Marshall and Lily try to get each other aroused. Robin doesn&#39;t understand Ted&#39;s mother&#39;s reaction to her.">Brunch</span></a></i>, whereÂ <a href="/wiki/Virginia_Mosby" title="Virginia Mosby">Ted's mother</a> also informs him that she is pregnant again.
</li></ul>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Future_References_.28Contains_Spoilers.29">Future References (Contains Spoilers)</span><span class="editsection"><a href="/wiki/How_Lily_Stole_Christmas?action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit Future References (Contains Spoilers) section"><img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D" class="sprite edit-pencil" />Edit</a></span></h2>
<ul><li>Future Ted continues to censor adult activities and swear words throughout the series, including:
<ul><li>"<a href="/wiki/Eating_a_sandwich" title="Eating a sandwich" class="mw-redirect">Eating a sandwich</a>" to mean smoking marijuana, first used inÂ <i><a href="/wiki/How_I_Met_Everyone_Else" title="How I Met Everyone Else"><span style="cursor: help;" title="How I Met Everyone Else (3x05) - Ted brings his new girlfriend to meet the group. Barney tries to prove she&#39;s on the wrong side of the line on his Hot/Crazy Scale. In the meantime, the gang tell stories about how they all met.">How I Met Everyone Else</span></a></i>.
</li><li>"Stuff" to mean "shit" inÂ <i><a href="/wiki/Murtaugh" title="Murtaugh"><span style="cursor: help;" title="Murtaugh (4x19) - Ted and Barney challenge each other to things they are too old and too young to do, respectively. Marshall helps Lily coach kindergarten basketball.">Murtaugh</span></a></i>.
</li><li>A "thumbs up" to mean giving someone the finger inÂ <i><a href="/wiki/Robin_101" title="Robin 101"><span style="cursor: help;" title="Robin 101 (5x03) - Robin thinks Barney is cheating on her, but instead he&#39;s been taking &quot;Robin 101&quot; classes from Ted. Meanwhile, Marshall tries to give away his barrel, but is upset that no one seems to want it.">Robin 101</span></a></i>.
</li><li>"Playing the bagpipes" to mean having sex inÂ <i><a href="/wiki/Bagpipes" title="Bagpipes"><span style="cursor: help;" title="Bagpipes (5x06) - Lily and Marshall have relationship problems, while Ted tries to determine if Barney and Robin&#39;s relationship is really going as well as it appears.">Bagpipes</span></a></i>.
</li><li>"Kiss" to mean "fuck" inÂ <i><a href="/wiki/The_Wedding_Bride" title="The Wedding Bride"><span style="cursor: help;" title="The Wedding Bride (5x23) - Tony&#39;s movie, The Wedding Bride, is released. It turns out to be based entirely around the wedding between Ted and Stella and Tony&#39;s involvement. However, in the movie, Ted is a villian and Tony is a hero. The gang all see the movie and reflect upon it.">The Wedding Bride</span></a></i>.
</li></ul>
</li><li>Ted's mother and Clint get married inÂ <i><a href="/wiki/Home_Wreckers" title="Home Wreckers"><span style="cursor: help;" title="Home Wreckers (5x20) - Ted reacts to his mother&#39;s second marriage by buying a house. Barney makes fun of Robin for crying at the wedding.">Home Wreckers</span></a></i>.
</li><li>Marshall's love for Christmas and Christmas decorations is shown again in <i><a href="/wiki/Symphony_of_Illumination" title="Symphony of Illumination"><span style="cursor: help;" title="Symphony of Illumination (7x12) - When Robin receives bad news, she decides to lie about it to the gang. Meanwhile, Marshall hangs Christmas decorations on the house in the â€˜burbs with help from his neighbor.">Symphony of Illumination</span></a></i>.
</li></ul>
